{"type":"document","pre_blank":0,"children":[{"type":"section","children":[{"type":"keyword","key":"title","value":"Org2JSON","post_blank":0},{"type":"keyword","key":"author","value":"Stephen Heywood","post_blank":2}]},{"type":"headline","level":1,"children":[{"type":"title","level":1,"raw":"Synopsis","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Synopsis"}]},{"type":"section","children":[{"type":"paragraph","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"While "},{"type":"link","path":"https://orgmode.org/","desc":"Org mode"},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"link","path":"https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/","desc":"Emacs"},{"type":"text","value":" are a great combination with a great ecosystem that can be extended in so many ways, there are times when it needs to interact with other systems."}]},{"type":"paragraph","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The goal of "},{"type":"link","path":"https://github.com/heyste/org2json","desc":"org2json"},{"type":"text","value":" is to build on top of the work done by "},{"type":"link","path":"https://github.com/PoiScript/orgize/blob/master/README.md","desc":"orgize"},{"type":"text","value":", a parsing library (with various "},{"type":"link","path":"https://github.com/PoiScript/orgize/tree/master/examples","desc":"examples"},{"type":"text","value":"), and provide an executable for generating json from any org file."}]}]}]},{"type":"headline","level":1,"children":[{"type":"title","level":1,"raw":"Using [[https://www.docker.com][Docker]]","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using "},{"type":"link","path":"https://www.docker.com","desc":"Docker"}]},{"type":"headline","level":2,"children":[{"type":"title","level":2,"raw":"Convert .org to .json","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Convert .org to .json"}]},{"type":"section","children":[{"type":"paragraph","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The following command will map the current folder inside the docker container, process "},{"type":"verbatim","value":"README.org"},{"type":"text","value":" and then save the json output as the file "},{"type":"verbatim","value":"README.json"},{"type":"text","value":". Also, it's going to delete the container when finished."}]},{"type":"source-block","contents":"docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/docs heyste/org2json /app/org2json /docs/README.org > README.json\n","language":"bash","arguments":"","post_blank":1}]}]},{"type":"headline","level":2,"children":[{"type":"title","level":2,"raw":"Using jq","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using jq"}]},{"type":"section","children":[{"type":"paragraph","post_blank":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With other tools like "},{"type":"link","path":"https://stedolan.github.io/jq/","desc":"jq"},{"type":"text","value":" it's possible to explore the json structure of a document."}]},{"type":"source-block","contents":"docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/docs heyste/org2json /app/org2json /docs/README.org | jq .children[0]\n","language":"bash","arguments":" :eval never-export :exports both","post_blank":1},{"type":"keyword","key":"RESULTS","value":"","post_blank":0},{"type":"source-block","contents":"{\n  \"type\": \"section\",\n  \"children\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"keyword\",\n      \"key\": \"title\",\n      \"value\": \"Org2JSON\",\n      \"post_blank\": 0\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"keyword\",\n      \"key\": \"author\",\n      \"value\": \"Stephen Heywood\",\n      \"post_blank\": 2\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","language":"bash","arguments":"","post_blank":0}]}]}]}]}
